snippet.textDisplay:
I was thinking about this recently, I can only think of a couple female artists in kpop that sing about female issues and female empowerment.  I'm in the right place.  

Kpop does not have a female-empowered girl group; a girl group that writes and produces their own songs that sing about female issues, heroines, unfairness, etc?  Where is that girl group that gives women a voice?  Would the birthrate go up in South Korea if there were programs to support single parenting and artificial insemination?  Did we not see an idol go to Japan to get this procedure done and give birth because it was not practiced in S.Korea?  Women might want children, but they do not want to be stuck in a loveless marriage, or have children that could be taken away from them when the husband gets tired and divorces her.  These are just the brim of many issues.
